article.headline: Wright St. 54, St. Bonaventure 45
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio (AP) -- Vaughn Duggins scored 16 points to lead Wright State to a 54-45 victory over St. Bonaventure Tuesday night. Wright State (5-3) led for the final 30 minutes of the game, which saw both teams shoot under 40 percent from the field. St. Bonaventure (5-7) led by 5 roughly 2:30 into the game, but then fell behind by 12 with 3:38 left to go in the first half thanks to a three-pointer by Duggins. After closing out the half on a 9-2 run, St. Bonaventure pulled within five. After St. Bonaventure fell behind by 10 nearly halfway through the second half, they were able to close within four points three different times. St. Bonaventure pulled within three with nearly six minutes to go but got no closer than five the rest of the way. Hillary Haley led St. Bonaventure with 16 points.
